=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFPulse_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring instant attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -4.0765
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1092
  pitch_clarity: 10.8509
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -16.7378
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFPulse Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFPulse.html
// Tags: LFPulse, Classes, oscillator, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
{ LFPulse.ar(50) * 0.1 }.play;
